			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Molten steel is a process used during the melting and refining of steel to remove or chemically combine oxygen from the molten steel to prevent porosity when it solidifies. It is a critical part of steel manufacturing, a significant industry with a substantial impact on the global economy. The process creates equal oxidization throughout the molten metal, removing excess carbon and vaporizing or binding impurities like silicon, phosphorus, and manganese.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">熔融钢是钢铁熔化和精炼过程中使用的一种工艺，目的是去除或化学合成钢水中的氧气，以防止钢水凝固时产生气孔。它是钢铁制造的关键部分，是对全球经济具有重大影响的重要行业。该工艺在整个熔融金属中产生均等的氧化作用，去除多余的碳，蒸发或结合硅、磷和锰等杂质。</common:generalComment>
